node.text:
Taking over Frankie’s account as a part of #TransTakeOver, founded by @ashleemariepreston! 

Tiiiiny bit about me:
I am an artist who identifies Deaf, trans, Jewish, and Chinese. My background includes launching a clothing line with Opening Ceremony, writing as a columnist for Condé Naste’s first queer publication - @Them, and being casted as a queer superhero within Warner Brother’s DC Universe, Titans.

Giving this talk two years ago felt as if I was opening up my diary and reading it to a crowd. It pinpoints three revelations I reached at the beginning of my gender journey.

I would love to know what you think about it!

ps: I answer your most curious questions on Frankie’s Instagram story today ;) #TransgenderAwarenessWeek

node.text: Yay! I can finally tell you all! I am starring in a move alongside these incredible boys and we just wrapped shooting! 🌟It is an entirely #lgbtq leading cast with #lgbt directors, making shooting it a beautiful way to have spent my #pride. This camp horror comedy will have you screaming and laughing all night long. 😂🔪We literally JUST finished shooting so I don’t have an official release date or anything but at least you know what I’ve been up to. 🎬Thank you Alex & Wes for writing and casting me as Nico and steering this ship of dreams. Thank you Travis, Noah & Troy for being my witchy coven sisters for this entire journey. 🧙🏼And thank you Michael for being so kind and funny. I love you all and can’t wait for you to see #SummoningSylvia! 👻🏳️‍🌈
